    "claim": "The pool never records how much ETH or token debt the orderbook owes to each token pool. `transferETHToOrderbook` / `transferTokenToOrderbook` debit whichever pool the caller names, while `receiveETHFromOrderbook` / `receiveTokenFromOrderbook` can later credit any pool the caller chooses, with no check that the repayment matches the originating pool.",
    "impact": "A buggy or compromised orderbook can silently move principal from one pool to another. LPs in the debited pool can be left insolvent, while a different pool receives an unearned windfall. This breaks pool-level solvency and lets losses be socialized onto unrelated LPs.",
    "paths": [
      "Borrow ETH from pool A with `transferETHToOrderbook(tokenA, amount)`.",
      "Repay the same ETH into pool B with `receiveETHFromOrderbook(tokenB, amount)`.",
      "Pool A LPs are now short the borrowed ETH, while pool B LPs gain assets they never funded."
    ]
  },
