    "claim": "The contract tracks no per-asset receivable and enforces no settlement price when the orderbook borrows one side of the pool and returns the other. Because `totalLiquidity` is just a raw sum of token units and wei, the orderbook can drain valuable ETH (or tokens) and later restore bookkeeping with an economically tiny amount of the opposite asset.",
